Company: Crypto.news
Salary: $45k - $74k est.
Our readers can safely rely on crypto news to stay up to date with the latest developments in the crypto industry.
Tasks
Conduct in-depth research and analysis of cryptocurrency markets, including fundamental, technical, and sentiment analysis;
Write comprehensive articles based on market data;
Write a weekly newsletter;
Monitor and interpret market trends, news, and events to identify opportunities and risks for various digital assets;
Produce high-quality research reports, whitepapers, and presentations on specific cryptocurrencies, projects, and industry trends;
Stay abreast of technological advancements and market dynamics shaping the crypto landscape;
High attention to detail as well as high confidence to make educated decisions and opinions.
Requirements
2+ years of proven experience in financial analysis, research, or investment management, preferably in the cryptocurrency or fintech industry.
Excellent analytical skills with the ability to source and interpret complex data and trends
Strong understanding of cryptocurrency markets, blockchain technology, and DeFi
The ability to write long-form research about complex narratives and ideas in a way that is clear, cohesive, accurate, and can be understood by a broad audience.
Familiarity with all of the tools in the industry that are available to support you in the research process.
Passion for innovation and a willingness to adapt to a fast-paced and evolving industry.
Effective communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to distill complex concepts into clear and actionable insights.
Benefits
Remote work with flexible hours;
Creative team, vibrant environment, and adequate leadership;
Work in a fast-paces and growing startup company;
